<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module has NONE. Every idiom it ships is the canon read correctly: the records and the
    hand-written value class hold immutable state, the enum singleton exposes no mutable field, and
    the sealed hierarchy is handled by an exhaustive switch — so the representation-exposure family
    (EI_EXPOSE_REP / EI_EXPOSE_REP2) and the equals/hashCode detectors stay quiet without any
    suppression. The filter is kept (empty) so a future, genuinely-reviewed suppression has a home
    with a reason, rather than being added inline.
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
